# Sidebar Single-Open Accordion + Sub-Route Hubs Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Enhance the Sidebar navigation to operate as a single-open accordion. Ensure that every sidebar sub-item navigates to a dedicated page (or "Module Hub") where the page title (H1) dynamically updates to match the clicked sub-item, and the page renders the specific requested tabs. This approach heavily relies on URL state (`?view=` inside `TabsContainer`) to sync internal tabs while updating the surrounding hub layout.

## Proposed Changes

### Part A: Sidebar Behavior Fix (Accordion)
#### [MODIFY] `client/src/components/layout/DashboardLayout.tsx`
- Replace `expandedSections: Record<string, boolean>` with a single `activeSectionKey: string | null`.
- Update the initialization logic from `localStorage` (`sidebar_active_section_v1`) to read/write a single string.
- Update `toggleSection(id)` to set `activeSectionKey` to `id` (if not already active) or `null` (if currently active).
- Update the rendering check to `isExpanded = activeSectionKey === item.id`.
- The auto-expand logic on mount/navigate will set the `activeSectionKey` to the parent matched by the current path.

### Part B: Sub-Item Pages (Module Hubs)
We will transition primary pages into "Module Hubs". Each hub will read the `?view=` parameter (or `?tab=`) to dynamically render the correct **H1 Title** and a configured `TabsContainer`.

#### [1] Alerts Hub
- **Modify:** `AlertsPage.tsx`
- **Logic:** Read `?view=` (all, unread, high, response). Render Title based on view. Pass `view` filter down to `AlertsList.tsx`.

#### [2] Performance Intelligence Hub
- **Modify:** `PerformancePage.tsx`
- **Logic:** Read `?view=` (continuous, kpi, underperformance). Render Title based on view. Render nested `TabsContainer` containing the required internal tabs for that view (e.g. Individual, Teams, Time Comparison for Continuous Analysis).

#### [3] Attrition Hub
- **Modify:** `AttritionPage.tsx`
- **Logic:** Similar to Performance. Sub-views are `risk`, `drivers`, `cost`.

#### [4] Training Hub
